{
  "//": "rio-fetcher seccomp profile (Localhost). ADR-019 §Sandbox hardening. Derived from seccomp-rio-builder.json with extra denies for ptrace/bpf/setns/process_vm_*/keyctl/add_key — fetchers face the open internet; a compromised upstream serving an exploit payload (curl/git CVE) could pivot to the node without these guards. The FOD hash check catches content tampering but not a rooted fetcher process.",
  "//provenance": "seccomp-rio-builder.json is itself derived from Docker/moby default.json v27.5.1, flattened to OCI runtime spec format for the executor cap set (CAP_SYS_ADMIN + CAP_SYS_CHROOT). The fetcher profile adds an explicit SCMP_ACT_ERRNO block for the 7 syscalls ADR-019 calls out — most were already denied-by-omission under the builder profile (defaultAction=ERRNO, not in any ALLOW block), but the explicit block makes the intent grep-able and guards against future allowlist widening accidentally re-enabling them.",
  "//denied-explicit": {
    "ptrace": "debugger attach — lets an escapee inspect/modify other processes sharing the PID namespace",
    "bpf": "load eBPF programs — kernel-side code execution surface",
    "setns": "join another namespace — defeats namespace isolation (executor CREATES namespaces via unshare/clone, never JOINS existing ones)",
    "process_vm_readv": "cross-process memory read without ptrace — same attack class as ptrace",
    "process_vm_writev": "cross-process memory write without ptrace",
    "keyctl": "kernel keyring manipulation — fetcher has no legitimate need for persistent kernel keys",
    "add_key": "add to kernel keyring — paired with keyctl"
  },
  "//kept": "mount/umount/unshare/clone/pivot_root — FUSE + overlayfs + nix sandbox need these even in fetch mode (the FOD build script runs inside the same sandbox).",
  "//caveat": "ADR-019 warns this may be too strict for git-lfs/hg/svn FODs. Allowlist widens as real FODs hit denials; the VM test git-based FOD subtest is the canary.",
  "defaultAction": "SCMP_ACT_ERRNO",
  "defaultErrnoRet": 1,
  "architectures": [
    "SCMP_ARCH_X86_64",
    "SCMP_ARCH_X86",
    "SCMP_ARCH_X32",
    "SCMP_ARCH_AARCH64",
    "SCMP_ARCH_ARM"
  ],
